 @vuru  old growth forests in the US are mostly protected already, in Washington state they only harvest trees in areas that have already been harvested decades ago. Weyerhaeuser is the largest company in the timber industry in the Pacific Northwest and every location they harvest is replanted right away. I have family in the Aberdeen area and Weyerhaeuser has a huge nursery near there that grows millions of seedlings a year that are replanted. 

Weyerhaeuser was the main company that replanted the forest that was devastated by Mt St Helens back in the early 80's they planted over 18 million trees starting just 30 days after the eruption and for several years after the eruption. Here's a link https://www.seattlepi.com/local/article/Weyerhaeuser-harvests-first-timber-since-Mount-1165401.php

Also Weyerhaeuser plants hundreds of millions of trees each year, last year alone they planted 131,000,000 new trees, here's another link https://www.weyerhaeuser.com/sustainability/our-commitment/our-story/

